cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the problem of cell detection in microscopy images using a deep convolutional neural network and compressed sensing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the network using pixel space encoding, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of deep learning techniques for cell detection also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves experiments on benchmark datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
